ğŸ”¹ 16. How do you calculate year-over-year growth?

`sql
SELECT 
    Year,
    Sales,
    LAG(Sales) OVER (ORDER BY Year) AS PrevYearSales,
    (Sales - LAG(Sales) OVER (ORDER BY Year)) * 100.0 / LAG(Sales) OVER (ORDER BY Year) AS YoYGrowth
FROM SalesData;
`

